column5: WELL ITS THAT TIME OF YEAR AGAIN!!! SUNNY AND ALITTLE BIT OF OPEN WATER AND THE WHOLE STEELHEADING COMMUNITY SHOWS UP!!! EVEN SOME OF MY QUIET LITTLE SPOTS WERE FLOODED WITH GUYS(NOT SO QUIET ANYMORE I GUESS LOL)  HIT LIKE 5 TRIBS TODAY AND ALL WERE PACKED(WITH PEOPLE AND THE ODD FISH  LOL)  WATER WERE STAINED BUT GOOD!!!  WENT 2/2 MYSELF TODAY!!! NOT BAD CONSIDERING THE BUFFET OUT IN THE WATER  LOL  I LIKED IT BETTER WHEN IT WAS -20 OUT  LOL  TIME TO DUST OFF THE SHOULDER PADS I GUESS!!! LOL
Well, thats being a north shore TO Steelheader for ya!  Go south young man...
Nice bows CC, thanks for sharing.

Hey Scott  Great job out there!! 5 tribs?  Thought you were going ice fishing on Simcoe?? LOL.  Bly and I went scouting to a few tribs Saturday afternoon, but didn't like what we saw...but then again, what do we know?? haha.  We were thinking about it today, but family stuff got in the way...then the winds picked right up.  Since we dont know the good places to go, we decided to stay at home.  Serves us right..LOL  Awesome pics...cant wait to get out again...oh yeah...you wanted -20....looks like you'll get that Tuesday and Wednesday...go crazy out there!!! LOL
Beauty fish Scott.  Way to go!  Joey
Right on CC - thanks for the eye candy!  UF
TX ALL!! WELL ITS 4:20AM ON MONDAY NOW SO LETS SEE IF A WEEKDAY QUIETER  LOL 50K WIND GUSTS OUGHT TO KEEP SOME HOME  LOL
